<DocsPageTitle Path="Usage/Material">
    Blazorise Material 3 Usage Guide
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Build modern Blazor apps with Blazorise Material 3 and customize the experience with Material design tokens.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Blazorise Material is a <Anchor To="https://m3.material.io/" Target="Target.Blank">Material 3</Anchor> focused provider. It ships with provider styles, behavior, and Material Symbols font files, so you no longer need to download third-party Material CSS files manually.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Material 3 Design is a design system from Google. Blazorise Material is an independent Blazor implementation inspired by Material 3 principles.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    <Alert Color="Color.Info" Visible>
        <AlertDescription>
            <Strong>Note:</Strong> Before proceeding, ensure you have already created a Blazor project. If not, the simplest way to start with Blazorise is by using our <Anchor To="docs/templates" Title="Link to templates">Templates</Anchor>.
        </AlertDescription>
    </Alert>
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    <GuideSeeTheDemo Provider="CssProvider.Material" />
</DocsPageParagraph>

